    <p style="text-align:center; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;"><strong>Microsoft Azure &ndash; Monitor Static Web App using Front Door and Alerts.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>This is a guide to improve the reliability of the Static Web Apps (SWA) by implementing monitoring, custom alerts, custom domain, front door configuration, and setup all the environment.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Resources needed:</p>
    <ul style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;">
        <li class="ListParagraph" style="margin-left:28.06pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:7.94pt; font-family:serif;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Custom domain and DNS zone previously created.</span></li>
        <li class="ListParagraph" style="margin-left:28.06pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:7.94pt; font-family:serif;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Static Web App - Standard.</span></li>
        <li class="ListParagraph" style="margin-left:28.06pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:7.94pt; font-family:serif;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Front Door &ndash; Standard/Premium.</span></li>
        <li class="ListParagraph" style="margin-left:28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; font-family:serif;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">GitHub repository.</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>Section 1 &ndash; Creating the Static Web App.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s create a new resource group.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then let&rsquo;s create a new repository on GitHub and upload the Static Web App content:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="668" height="199" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then, create the Static Web App in the Azure portal.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="147" height="185" alt="Text

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Fill the data:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="497" height="487" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="497" height="191" alt=""></p>
    <p>After the creation of the Static Web App, go to the GitHub portal and check the Actions, verify that there is no problem to run the workflow.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="262" height="133" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then, you will be able to visit your new Static Web App using the Funny Name (default URL of the SWA).</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="445" height="205" alt="Graphical user interface, application, Word

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s recap:</p>
    <p>We have created a new GitHub repository, then a SWA and deployed the content.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p><strong>Section 2 &ndash; Creating the Azure Front Door.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>GGo back to the resource group, at this point we have only the SWA, so we are going to create the Azure Front Door.</p>
    <p>Click on Create, in the Market place look up for Front Door and CDN profiles:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="733" height="386" alt="Graphical user interface, text

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Configure the Front Door information and create the resource:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="602" height="658" alt="Graphical user interface, text

Description automatically generated"><span style="width:227.25pt; display:inline-block;">&nbsp;</span></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Now the Front Door is created</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="154" height="64" alt="Text

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s recap: We have created the SWA and the Azure Front Door.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>Section 3 &ndash; Configuration of the Front Door.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let configure the Front Door to be able to reach the Static Web App.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="167" height="32" alt="" style="float: left; ">Go to <strong>Front Door manager</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>You will see that there is an Endpoint configured and also the Security policy:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="756" height="190" alt="A screenshot of a computer screen

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="395" height="178" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p>Use the default endpoint URL to go to your SWA through the Azure Front Door  (use https://&lt;URL&gt;)</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="543" height="263" alt="Graphical user interface, application, website

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Now the SWA is configured to use a Front Door, and the Front Door is able to reach the SWA.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s improve the security by modifying the Front Door endpoint to allow connections only under HTTPS protocol.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="716" height="188" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;In Accepted protocols select HTTPS only:</p>
    <p style="margin-left:18pt;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="411" height="142" alt="Graphical user interface

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p style="margin-left:18pt;">&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In Forwarding protocol, change from Match incoming request option to HTTPS only:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="436" height="88" alt="Graphical user interface

Description automatically generated with low confidence"></p>
    <p>Then, click on <strong>update</strong> to apply the changes</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Now let configure the Static Web App to allow connection only from the Front Door by modifying the staticwebapp.config.json file:</p>
    <p>Go to the GitHub repository, open the staticwebapp.config.json file:</p>
    <p><span style="height:0pt; display:block; position:absolute; z-index:1;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="676" height="204" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated" style="margin: 0 auto 0 0; display: block; "></span>Then click on &lsquo;Edit&rsquo; button</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Check the Actions tab of the repository:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="387" height="191" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Now, if you want to go to the Static Web App using the Funny Name (custom URL), you will get a Forbidden message:</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="756" height="254" alt="Graphical user interface

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>Section 4 &ndash; Configuring custom domain for Front Door Endpoint.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Go to Front Door manager</p>
    <p><span style="height:0pt; display:block; position:absolute; z-index:-1;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="167" height="32" alt="" style="margin: 0 auto 0 0; display: block; "></span>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Click on Edit route</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="756" height="196" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In the Domain section, click on Add new domain</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="612" height="101" alt="Graphical user interface, text

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>Select the DNS Zone</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="460" height="234" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application, chat or text message

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>Click on Add new, to create the custom domain, or select one from the list.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="489" height="232" alt=""></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="349" height="46" alt="Text

Description automatically generated" style="float: left; ">You will get this alert:</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>The domain needs to be validated.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Click on add.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then you will see both domains available for your endpoint:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="347" height="141" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"><br>ou can choose if maintain both or disable the default domain.</p>
    <p>Click on Update to apply the changes.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>After applying the changes, you will see the second domain listed in the endpoint:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="377" height="168" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Click on the domain, then you will see that the domain validation is needed and the validation state is Pending</p>
    <p><span style="height:0pt; display:block; position:absolute; z-index:2;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="122" height="72" alt="Graphical user interface, website

Description automatically generated" style="margin: 0 auto 0 0; display: block; "></span><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="566" height="87" alt="Graphical user interface, text, website

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Click on the Pending link, this will open a menu to Validate the custom domain:</p>
    <p><span style="height:0pt; display:block; position:absolute; z-index:5;"><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAOIAAAASCAYAAABGggLOAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABbSURBVHhe7cmxDcAwAMOw/P90G3j27CwUwEnn9gFPpTaAndQGsJPaAHZSG8BOagPYSW0AO6kNYCe1AeykNoCd1Aawk9oAdlIbwE5qA9hJbQA7qQ1gR5Ik3c75AcTmAsNK5INkAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC" width="226" height="18" alt="" style="margin: 0 0 0 auto; display: block; "></span><span style="height:0pt; display:block; position:absolute; z-index:6;"><img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAOIAAAASCAYAAABGggLOAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABbSURBVHhe7cmxDcAwAMOw/P90G3j27CwUwEnn9gFPpTaAndQGsJPaAHZSG8BOagPYSW0AO6kNYCe1AeykNoCd1Aawk9oAdlIbwE5qA9hJbQA7qQ1gR5Ik3c75AcTmAsNK5INkAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC" width="226" height="18" alt="" style="margin: 0 0 0 auto; display: block; "></span><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="541" height="536" alt="Graphical user interface

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="532" height="34" alt="" style="float: left; "></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then click on Domain validation needed on Certificate static, and click on update.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="154" height="73" alt="Graphical user interface, text, website

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>After this step, you will need to wait around 10-20 minutes to complete the process of validation.</p>
    <p>Additionally, you can add an extra CNAME record on your DNS Zone, the previous custom domain but pointing to the default URL of the endpoint.</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="314" height="289" alt="Graphical user interface

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>When the verification concludes, you will be able to see your both custom domains for your endpoint:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="437" height="236" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="444" height="188" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated" style="float: left; ">Now we can go to the Static Web App using the custom domain configured to the endpoint (make sure you are using HTTPS protocol on the URL):</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>Section 5 &ndash; Configuring the alert for 4XX responses.</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In the left panel menu, under monitoring section go to Alerts, then click on Action groups, then create.<br><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="537" height="60" alt="">&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Fill the information</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="485" height="344" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Move to the Notifications tab:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="722" height="180" alt=""></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Then configure the email information:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="522" height="681" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>After configured the email information, move to Review + create and create the action group, after that wait a few minutes to see the action group created.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Now go to Alerts, Create and select Alert rule:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="365" height="134" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>Select Percentage of 4XX</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="168" height="40" alt=""></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;Then configure the configure the Condition</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="531" height="237" alt=""></p>
    <p>Configure the Split by dimensions: Endpoint = your endpoint previously configured:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="588" height="158" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>Then move to the Actions tab and select the action group recently created<br><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="681" height="390" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated">&nbsp;</p>
    <p>After that the rule will be created.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>For testing the alert, we can configure the staticwebapp.config.json to require authentication, as we did not configured any auth method in the SWA, the SWA will return a 401 Unauthorized, this will trigger the alert and the email alert will be sent.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s configure the test:</p>
    <p>Go to GitHub and modify the staticwebapp.config.json and add a property to allow only authenticated users by adding this property:</p>
    <p style="line-height:normal;"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="710" height="372" alt="Text

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>After adding the rule, check the workflow:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="329" height="165" alt="Graphical user interface, application

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>To trigger the alert, go to the SWA and refresh the page:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="439" height="296" alt="Graphical user interface, text, Word, email, website

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>This will trigger the alert, then in about 5-10 minutes, the alert will get received on the email:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="371" height="317" alt="Graphical user interface, text, application

Description automatically generated"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="318" height="224" alt="Table

Description automatically generated"></p>
    <p>It is possible to see the alert in the portal:</p>
    <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="447" height="120" alt="A screenshot of a computer

Description automatically generated with medium confidence"></p>
    <p>To re-enable your app to be accessible for all the customers, only remove the auth configuration from the staticwebapp.config.json.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Let&rsquo;s recap: At this point we have configured the Static Web App, the GitHub repository, the Front Door, the endpoint with custom domain, the alerts.</p>
